<subSubSection id="C30C657C892C9156FE5259F57B21B5DE" box="[406,796,917,941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BA936F7892C9156FE5259F57B21B5DE" blockId="1.[406,796,917,941]" box="[406,796,917,941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<heading id="D0E1819B892C9156FE5259F57B21B5DE" bold="true" box="[406,796,917,941]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FE5259F57B21B5DE" bold="true" box="[406,796,917,941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FE5259F57AECB5DE" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[406,721,917,941]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagonychiformis">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FE5259F57AECB5DE" bold="true" box="[406,721,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Lycocerus rhagonychiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C657C892C9156FFB559A67BD2B36F" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA936F7892C9156FFB559A67A62B2EF" blockId="1.[113,1089,965,1564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FFB559A678DBB5AF" bold="true" box="[113,230,965,988]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small size (about 
<quantity id="4CEE9B12892C9156FE7059A67A2FB5AF" box="[436,530,965,988]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
); small and not very prominent eyes; knife-shaped, subtriangular apical maxillary palpomere; filiform antennae, exceeding half of elytral length in male, extending to elytral midlength in female, without groove; subquadrate pronotum, narrower than head in male, nearly as wide as or slightly narrower than head in female; all claws simple in both sexes; abdominal ventrite VII of female with not well developed or indistinct median lobe; laterophyses of aedeagus long, visible in lateral view; long spermathecal duct; spermatheca provided with a spiral tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936F7892C9156FFB55EC67BD2B36F" blockId="1.[113,1089,965,1564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FFB55EC67957B2CF" bold="true" box="[113,362,1189,1212]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species-group resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FD685EC67B11B2CF" baseAuthorityName="Okushima" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[684,812,1189,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanatanii">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FD685EC67B11B2CF" box="[684,812,1189,1212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. hanatanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, which was defined and proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B06892C9156FE405EA67A7FB2AF" author="OKUSHIMA" box="[388,578,1221,1244]" firstAuthor="OKUSHIMA" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 383" refId="ref4333" refString="OKUSHIMA Y. 2005: A taxonomic study on the genus Lycocerus (Coleoptera, Cantharidae) from Japan, with zoogeographical considerations. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, Monographic Series 2: 1 - 383." type="book chapter" year="2005">OKUSHIMA (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FC4C5EA67C36B2AF" baseAuthorityName="Okushima" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[904,1035,1221,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanatanii">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FC4C5EA67C36B2AF" box="[904,1035,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. hanatanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by subtriangular apical maxillary palpomere; longer antennae in male; narrower pronotum, especially in male; laterophyses of aedeagus long, visible in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C657C892C9156FFB55F4678DDB06F" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA936F7892C9156FFB55F4678DDB06F" blockId="1.[113,1089,965,1564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FFB55F4678DDB34F" bold="true" box="[113,224,1317,1340]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B06892C9156FF215F467995B34F" author="HSIAO" box="[229,424,1317,1340]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="HSIAO" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref4188" refString="HSIAO Y., OKUSHIMA Y., YANG P. - S. &amp; KO C. - C. 2016. Taxonomic revision of the Lycocerus hanatanii species group (Coleoptera, Cantharidae), with the description of new species from Taiwan. European Journal of Taxonomy 170: 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2016">HSIAO et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
revised 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FDC45F467ABCB34F" baseAuthorityName="Okushima" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[512,641,1317,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanatanii">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FDC45F467ABCB34F" box="[512,641,1317,1340]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. hanatanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by adding several members from 
<collectingCountry id="F3017667892C9156FF6E5F2678C5B32F" box="[170,248,1349,1372]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F3017667892C9156FE565F2679E8B32F" box="[402,469,1349,1372]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">China</collectingCountry>
. They used the morphological-based phylogenetic analysis including all the defined species-groups to support their classification. The clade 
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FC1F5F0679AFB3EF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FC1F5F0678D2B3EF" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagonychiformis">L. rhagonychiformis</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FECB5FE679AFB3EF" baseAuthorityName="Okushima" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[271,402,1413,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanatanii">L. hanatanii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
species-group is supported in the resultant strict consensus tree. We herein propose a new species-group, 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FDDE5FC67B75B3CF" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[538,840,1445,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagonychiformis">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FDDE5FC67B75B3CF" box="[538,840,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">Lycocerus rhagonychiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group including 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FC3D5FC67981B3AF" authority="(Wittmer, 1983)" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhagonychiformis">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FC3D5FC67937B3AF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. rhagonychiformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B06892C9156FED35FA67989B3AF" author="Wittmer" box="[279,436,1477,1500]" firstAuthor="Wittmer" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" pagination="147 - 172" refId="ref4479" refString="WITTMER W. 1983: Die Familie Cantharidae (Col.) auf Taiwan (2. Teil). Entomological Review of Japan 38: 147 - 172." type="journal article" year="1983">Wittmer, 1983</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FE2B5FA67A43B3AF" authority="Hsiao &amp; Okushima, 2016" authorityName="Hsiao &amp; Okushima" authorityYear="2016" box="[495,638,1477,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wenchuani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FE2B5FA67A43B3AF" box="[495,638,1477,1500]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. wenchuani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A251579E892C9156FD405FA67AEAB3AF" box="[644,727,1477,1500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
based on its diagnostic characters separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D74892C9156FEDE5F8679A0B38F" baseAuthorityName="Okushima" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[282,413,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hanatanii">
<emphasis id="B962EAE5892C9156FEDE5F8679A0B38F" box="[282,413,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">L. hanatanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and the phylogenetic relationship suggested in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B06892C9156FC235F8678E0B06F" author="HSIAO" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="HSIAO" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref4188" refString="HSIAO Y., OKUSHIMA Y., YANG P. - S. &amp; KO C. - C. 2016. Taxonomic revision of the Lycocerus hanatanii species group (Coleoptera, Cantharidae), with the description of new species from Taiwan. European Journal of Taxonomy 170: 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2016">HSIAO et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
